 itself. The excerpts from his interviews provide a rarely afforded intimate look at these politicians. What emerges from these stories is a humane and believable portrait of public servants acting on behalf of the public good, a portrait that should provide some comfort, perhaps even inspiration, for citizens concerned about the state of American democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLegislatorszUnited StatesxStatesvInterviews. 0aPolitical participationzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aResponsibility. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / General.2bisacsh  aalienation.  acombats.  adistrust.  aeveryday.  aface.  afrom.  alife.  apersonal.  apolitians.  apolitical.  apublics.  aputting.  athis.  awork.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081477575240uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814776858.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814776858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814776858/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK